On Thursday, International Federation of Athletics Federations president Sebastian Coe praised Russia for its apology for the doping scandal, saying the apology was “candid,” but he reiterated that now is not the time for Russia to re-join the sport.
Mitri Chiracdin, president of the Russian Athletics Federation, said at the IAAF convention on the eve of the World Athletics Championships that his country was right to be banned from the sport and that he was determined to fight doping.
He said he regretted that “all athletes who won gold and silver medals in the competition were stripped of their medals”.
Despite his comments, the IAAF voted in favor of maintaining the ban. Previously, the World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) report mentioned the discovery of evidence of state-sponsored doping, which was implemented in November 2015.
“I think today’s response was very candid, very candid,” IAAF President Kek told reporters.
“The entire Council and the AAL General Assembly are pleased ... the Russian Federation admits that it has been through a very burning period and is doing everything possible to ensure that Russia can re-enter the competition.”
