“I think it’s been a very constructive day and also think we’ve made some progress, but the AAF General Assembly supports the task force’s recommendations and it’s not time to restore eligibility for Russia,” Ko said.
“We need to do everything we can in the next few months to normalize this situation.”
Our guiding principle has always been the desire to separate innocent athletes from contaminated systems,” he added.
Nineteen Russian athletes, meeting the strict standards of the IAAF, will compete as neutrals at the World Athletics Championships in London on Friday.
