But at the same time, the self-driving tour market, which is expected to break through the trillion scale, is also facing a double challenge.
In the context of consumption upgrading and free travel, self-driving travel is encouraged by national policies and more and more consumers are loved.
But at the same time, is expected to break through the trillion scale of the self-driving travel market is also facing a double challenge, on the one hand, the development of self-driving travel industry and market demand is not proportional, self-driving travel clubs and travel agencies and other self-driving tour organizers are facing a meager profit dilemma; on the other hand, the infrastructure and services facing self-driving travel are still in the initial stage.
60% of the total number of domestic tourists, the market size is expected to break the trillion
In 2016, 4.44 billion domestic tourism trips, self-driving travel accounted for about 60% of the total number of domestic tourism, and the scale of self-driving travel is expected to exceed trillions by 2020.
According to the statistics of the China Tourism Vehicle and Boat Association on the number of self-driving trips, the number of people from driving has continued to grow in the past five years, and the proportion of tourists accounting for the domestic tourist number is stable at more than half.
At the same time, the region and the national level have shown more attention and support for self-driving travel, and from 2016 to 2017, policies and regulations related to self-driving cars, sojourners and camping tourism were intensively introduced.
In July 2017, the National Tourism Administration, the State Sports Administration and other eight departments jointly issued the "Automobile Sports Camp Development Plan"; in the same month, the Development and Reform Commission, the Ministry of Finance and other 14 departments jointly issued the "Promotion of Rural Tourism Development Quality Improvement and Upgrading Action Plan (2017)", self-driving travel was highlighted.
The introduction of policies has provided opportunities and policy guidance for the development of domestic self-driving tourism.
Self-driving tour club profit is meager, the complete industrial chain is the key
Although the domestic self-driving tourism market has great potential and national policies are actively guided, the self-driving tourism industry is still in its infancy.
According to the "2016-2017 China Self-Driving Tour Annual Development Report", there are thousands of domestic self-driving clubs, car clubs, and car owners, but the proportion of tourists self-driving trips accounts for the majority, and only about 15% of tourists participate in various institutions such as ride-hailing clubs and self-driving clubs.
At the same time, independent research and development of self-driving travel products of online travel enterprises and traditional travel agencies are also a handful, many online travel platforms sell only some of the suppliers to provide self-driving travel products, some self-driving travel clubs are also important suppliers.
From the organization of self-driving activities, covering "eat, live, travel, travel, purchase, entertainment" a number of aspects, high degree of fragmentation, upstream supply chain heavy, tourists spend randomness.
Li Guanjie, founder and CEO of Beijing Xingtian Automobile Club, believes that self-driving travel clubs are essentially similar to travel agencies, and the early main profit models are mainly based on offline activities, and the core point is self-driving tour line products and leader services.
However, now that the homogenization of line products in the field of self-driving travel is serious, the level of leadership service is uneven, and the self-driving tour club is facing the need for another transformation.
It can be seen that self-driving travel itself is not an independent industry, but with the displacement characteristics of self-driving travel to form a cross-regional, industry ecological circle, the formation of a complete industrial chain is very important.
Experts pointed out that in addition to basic tourism consumption, experience is a more important consumption element.
Therefore, for the development of the self-driving tourism industry, the experience characteristics should be enhanced, and the theme of "self-driving tour +" should be developed and the IP of self-driving travel products.
The scenic road is not only a road, the car camp should not only meet the accommodation.
In the face of the rise of self-driving travel, the basic supporting development of self-driving travel is also relatively junior.
Li Guanjie pointed out that the tourist scenic road is not just a road, but the need to integrate the elements of transportation and tourism, but the road and tourism itself are responsible for the two departments, the transportation department to increase the tourism elements, but also stay in the construction of toilets, consulting centers, publicity columns and other facilities, and the combination of tourism is not high.
Compared with the well-known self-driving route "American Route 66", the construction experience is worth learning from.
The landscape design is no longer the most direct and fast path between the departure point to the destination, but follows the design concept of "experiment driving pleasure" to provide self-driving tourists with the best enjoyment of the beautiful scenery along the road; the scenic road can connect the point-shaped and face-like tourism landscape, which not only retains the historical value and cultural value of the eco-tourism resources along the route, but also can hold various thematic activities to enhance the participation and leisure experience of tourists and create economic benefits for the local tourism industry.
In addition to the scenic road, the camp is also an important supporting facility for self-driving tours.
However, among the self-driving tourists who are known to the Beijing News reporter, there are not many consumers who choose to stay in the camp.
They believe that many camps are biased towards infrastructure, can only meet the needs of eating and living, the grade is not high, and the product is single, which cannot meet the needs of self-driving travel, which contains many elements.
Some people in the industry who did not want to be named said that many of the companies that did the camp in the past few years were to take land, and after taking the land, the supporting infrastructure construction and services in the later period did not keep up, and many of the operating conditions were losses, and without the late capital injection, it was difficult to do some corresponding supporting products.
Consumer groups
According to the data released by the China Tourism Vehicle and Boat Association in 2017, from the perspective of age, the self-driving tour group is concentrated in 21-40 years old, especially between 31 and 40 years old, which has a certain economic foundation, and the demand for personalized tourism is high, and most of them are parent-child travel customers.
From the accommodation survey, self-driving tourists have a relative preference for non-standard accommodation.
From the perspective of self-driving travel, the surrounding self-driving is the most important type of self-driving travel, accounting for 84.32%.
Driving abroad is the yearning of many people, but the proportion is still small.
At the same time, with the increase of consumer demand, tourists who used to like to drive to "visit attractions" began to change their concepts, no longer "take pictures and sleep in the car" during the self-driving tour, but pay more attention to the experience and process of travel.
Dinosaurs use camouflage to avoid enemies
At first glance, it looks terrible, but it looks like a statue.
The researchers released the first work on the incredible fossils found by Canadian miners the size of rhinos, pointing out that the fossil is well preserved, so experts call it the "Mona Lisa of the Dinosaur World".
The fossil is well preserved, and it can even be concluded that its squamous skin is reddish-brown. This suggests that it has had some "annoying experiences."
A report in the journal Current Biology describes it as "the best-preserved dinosaur ever found and one of the best dinosaur specimens in the world."
The fossil is a newly discovered species of nodule dragon that lived between 110 million and 11.2 million years ago in the mid-Cretaceous period.
It was remarkably well preserved, shocking researchers who described it as “really breathtaking.”
According to National Geographic, the herbivorous dinosaur fossil is the best-preserved dinosaur fossil ever found.
On March 21, 2011, Shawn Funk discovered the fossil while mining at the Senkel Millennium Mine near Fort McMurray in northern Alberta, Canada.
At that time, he came across something that seemed not to be the same as the rocks around him, so he decided to look at it carefully.
After that, the fossils he found were sent to the Royal Canadian Museum of Terrell Paleontology.
It took six years for the researchers to bring the beast inside the 2,500-pound (1,100 kg) cart to its true face.
After such a hard work, the final results are now announced.
"If you look at it, you're almost sure it's sleeping," said Caleb Brown, a scientist at the Royal Tyrell Museum and the first author. The creature is on display at the exhibition.
“It will be one of the most beautiful and well-preserved dinosaur specimens in the history of science – the Mona Lisa in the dinosaur world.”
By studying its skin, the researchers found that the herbivorous creature, although dressed in armor, like a walking tank, was likely to be a major threat from a carnivorous dinosaur.
The dinosaur, which is heavily dressed in heavy armor, used red-and-white camouflage to avoid predators and used concealment known as "anti-shadowing", which was also used by many modern animals.
In this way, experts say, it is better able to blend in with its surroundings and thus avoid enemies, suggesting that it is preyed on by larger dinosaurs.
The 110-million-year-old creature, who is part of the denctional dragon family, made headlines for the first time in May and is currently on display at the Royal Tyrell Museum of Ancient Biology.
After one of the team members, Mark Mitchell, a museum technician, spent 7,000 hours carefully unveiling the beast, the researchers now studied it and named it “Borealopelta Markmitchelli.”
The samples were well preserved, allowing Dr. Mitchell, as well as an international team of scientists, to record the patterns and shapes of the scales and armor on their bodies.
They found “anti-shade”, a common defense in the animal kingdom, meaning the creature’s back was darker than its side color.
Although “anti-shadowing” is common, the findings are surprising because the dinosaur is far bigger than the existing animals that use anti-shadowing.
This dinosaur faced pressure to be hunted by meat-eating dinosaurs, and thus evolved in a favorable direction, allowing it to hide in the front as a means of survival.
However, most of the animals in existence that use anti-shadowing, such as deer, zebras or armadillos, are as small and vulnerable as prey, suggesting that the creature faces real pressure to survive.
“The wild predation of large heavy armor dinosaurs shows how dangerous it is for Cretaceous carnivorous dinosaurs,” Brown said.
Chemical analysis of the organic complex in its scales also indicates that the dinosaur’s skin color was reddish-browd.
Scientists are continuing to study the creature’s life cues, including the stomach content it retains, to find the last food to eat.
They believe that dinosaurs fell into the river at the time of their death, then washed into the sea, and finally sank to the bottom of the sea in a back-to-back descent.
At the time, Alberta’s climate was as warm as it was in southern Florida today, and rivers and oceans were likely to be deeper inland than they are now.
Brown said: "This nut noduly dragon is truly amazing, because it is completely covered with preserved squamous skin, and, to this day, it is preserved in the dimensional space, thus allowing its original shape to be preserved."
“So the creature is now in almost the same shape as it was in the Cretaceous.
You don't need to rebuild it with too much imagination; if you look at it, you'll almost believe it's sleeping."
The Cretaceous period was the period when two-legged large theropods roamed the earth.
Although Tyrannosaurus rex was the king of dinosaurs, it appeared millions of years after the draped dinosaurs. The dragon dinosaurs may have been hunted by some of the tyrannosaurs.
They include high-thornosaurus, a 6-ton, 38-foot-long (11.5-meter) behemoth.
New research has found that scientists who appear in the journal Current Biology believe that the knot dragon was washed into the sea after death and later formed a mummy in the soil.
On March 21, 2011, Sean Fink excavated the creature at a Millennium mine near Fort McMurray in Alberta, Canada.
According to the museum, it is the best preserved drape dinosaur in the world, and the skin and armor in the area from the nose to the hip are complete.
The average length of this creature is about 18 feet (5 meters) and weighs 3,000 pounds (1,300 kilograms).
It has two 20-inch-long sharp angles that protrude from the shoulder.
The researchers believe that this herbivore dinosaur was active in what is now western Canada, and was then washed into the sea by a flood-prone river.
However, the dinosaur's burial at the bottom of the sea allowed it to preserve its armor intact.
The fossil remains of this particular sample are well preserved, leaving the remaining skin still covered with uneven slices of the dinosaur skull.
As Michael Greshko wrote in National Geographic, this level of preservation is as rare as it is.
The more I look, the more I feel it is unbelievable.
Remnant skin fossils are still covered in the mottled armor of the dinosaur skull.
Its right front palm is on its side, and the five toes are unfolded upwards.
