No need to buy anymore!These more than 8,000 kinds of products zero tariff
At the regular press conference held by the Ministry of Commerce on January 11, the spokesman of the Ministry of Commerce said that as of now, there are 15 free trade agreements that have been implemented in China, involving 23 countries and regions, covering more than 8,000 kinds of zero-tariff imported products.
At the same time, imported cosmetics, Icelandic salmon, Chilean red wine, ASEAN tropical fruits... these products you want no longer need to spend a lot of money on behalf of the purchase.
At present, China has signed 16 free trade agreements with 24 countries and regions, and 15 have been implemented in force, covering more than 8,000 kinds of zero-tariff imported products.
Taking agricultural products as an example, with the implementation of the free trade agreement, consumers can taste agricultural products from different origins, high quality and low price throughout the year.
For example, tropical fruits such as durian, lychee, and dragon fruit in ASEAN have tariffs ranging from 15% to 30% to zero tariffs.
The import duty on Icelandic salmon is reduced from 10% to 12% to zero.
Wine imports from Georgia and Chile are reduced from 14% to 30% to zero.
There are also New Zealand's specialty agricultural products such as beef and milk powder, which have a large tax reduction.
Take industrial products, for example, the import tariffs on some cosmetics in Switzerland have been reduced to zero;
The import tariff on some watches has been reduced by 50%, and the tariff will be reduced to zero after a few years.
South Korea's refrigerators, rice cookers, massagers, beauty machines and other products import tariffs reduced by 40%, and will be reduced to zero tariffs in a few years;
